step.action:
Through natural PM-style conversation, refine and capture:
      - {{problem_statement}}
      - {{target_users}}
      - {{expected_outcome}}
      - {{business_value}}
      - {{constraints}}
      - {{scope_in}}
      - {{scope_out}}
      - {{success_signals}}

Define a single epic with:
      - {{epic_name}}
      - {{epic_summary}}
      - {{epic_goal}}
      - {{epic_priority}}
      - {{epic_success_metrics}}

Capture workspace-level technical outputs:
      - {{cross_story_dependencies}}
      - {{technical_risks}}
      - {{open_questions}}
      - {{recommended_implementation_order}}

For each story in {{stories}}, prepare {{story_md_content}} with this structure:

# Story: {{story.title}}
> Feature: {{feature_title}} | ID: {{story.id}} | Priorité: {{story.priority}}

## Contexte
{{story.user_outcome}}

## Acceptance Criteria
{{story.acceptance_criteria as numbered list}}

## Contraintes applicables
- DoD : context/dod.md
- NFR : {relevant NFR constraints for this story, extracted from context/nfr.md}

## Tasks
{{for each task in story.tasks:
  "- [ ] [{{task.kind}}] {{task.title}}
        {{task.description}}
        {{if task.technical_notes: '      Note: ' + task.technical_notes}}
        {{if task.depends_on: '      Dépend de: ' + task.depends_on | join(', ')}}"
}}

## Notes architecturales
{{story.architecture_notes or "Aucune"}}

## Risques
{{story.risks or "Aucun identifié"}}

---
Created via Nakiros plan-feature on {date}. Execute with /nak-workflow-dev-story.

step.output:
[PLAN-FEATURE] ✅ TERMINÉ
Feature : {{feature_title}}
Stories : {{stories | count}}
{{for each story: "  - {{story.id}} — {{story.title}}"}}

Prochaine étape : /nak-workflow-dev-story pour implémenter une story.
